# WarehouseJobs Core Invariants

Lean always-on summary. Full governance is canonical in the linked docs — read them when a task needs detail.

## Fail-Closed (overrides all other rules)

If information is missing, ambiguous, or conflicting: do NOT guess, do NOT proceed. STOP and ask.

## API Contract Rule (hard rule)

- `docs/api/openapi.yaml` is the source of truth for all endpoint signatures, request/response shapes, and error codes.
- No endpoint may be implemented that deviates from the spec without first updating the spec.
- No new endpoint may be added without first adding it to the spec.

## Architecture Boundaries

- Layering: Controllers (thin) → Domain Services (business logic) → Core capabilities (`src/api/src/core/*`) → Prisma / Redis / MinIO.
- Controllers validate input and call one service method. Services own business logic. No business logic in controllers.
- Cross-cutting types live in `src/api/src/core/`. Import from module barrels (`index.ts`) only.
- Domains never import another domain's internals. Only `src/core/` modules are `@Global()`.

## Quality Gates (STOP if any fails)

```bash
# Run from src/api/
npm run lint
npm run type-check
npm run test
npm run test:integration   # when DB/Redis touched
npm run test:e2e           # when HTTP surface touched
npm run test:cov           # >= 85% line coverage for changed services
```

Do not skip gates, bypass CI, or merge with known failures.

## Source Precedence (highest wins)

1. `CLAUDE.md` (constitution) 2. `AGENTS.md` (orchestration) 3. `docs/plan.md` (tasks/gates)
4. `docs/api/openapi.yaml` (API contract) 5. `docs/agent/standards/` 6. `.cursor/skills/` 7. `docs/agent/personas/` 8. `docs/agent/analysis/`

If `AGENTS.md` conflicts with `CLAUDE.md`, `CLAUDE.md` prevails.

